title: Keycap Digit Six

adjectives: Denoting a quantity consisting of six items or units
verbs: To determine the number (of objects in a group).
Determine the number or amount of
nouns: A concept of quantity involving zero and units
Mathematical object used to count, label, and measure
A number is one of several related types of mathematical objects.
A member of one of several classes: natural numbers, integers, rational numbers, real numbers, complex numbers, quaternions.
A set of numerals for representing numbers.
A piece of music composed for six voices or six instruments; a sextet or sestuor.
A sextet is a formation containing exactly six members.
6 is the natural number following 5 and preceding 7.
A numerical value equal to 6; the number occurring after five and before seven.
The cardinal number occurring after five and before seven, represented in Roman numerals as VI, in Arabic numerals as 6.

description: The number 6 on a square with rounded corners, designed to look like a keycap.
apple_vendor_description: Apple’s keycap digit six emoji is presented as a clean, crisp numeral '6' encased in a softly rounded, dark gray keycap, a hallmark of Apple’s consistent UI design. The subtle gloss and refined shading give it a tactile feel, suggesting a precise selection or input. On Apple devices, this emoji clearly denotes the number six, often used in sequences, for rankings, or when indicating a quantity or specific numerical choice within digital communication.
